 <
 
+                                                      *codediff-filler-text*
+Filler appearance~
+
+Alignment rows keep corresponding content at the same vertical position in
+side-by-side and conflict views. By default, these rows use a repeated
+slash pattern. Set a different text pattern or use an empty string to keep
+the alignment rows blank:
+>lua
+  require("codediff").setup({
+    diff = { filler_text = "· " },
+  })
+
+  require("codediff").setup({
+    diff = { filler_text = "" },
+  })
+<
+
+Non-empty patterns use the CodeDiffFiller highlight group. Inline deleted
+lines and move annotations are not filler rows and are unaffected.
+
